<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-699-877  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 699 877.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 23 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Macintosh: font conversion utility ships. (Evolution fromImage Club) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenbaum, Daniel J.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Image Club Graphics Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Evolution (Add-in/on software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionUtility ProgramsFonts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR MACINTOSH: Font Conversion Utility Ships 11/23/90 CALGARY, ALBERTA,CANADA, 1990 NOV 23 (NB) -- Evolution, a font editing utility from the fontand clip-art publisher Image Club, is shipping, company officials say.andP;  The$99 utility converts PostScript fonts into the proprietary format developedby Adobe.andM;Until Adobe published the specification for its &quot;hinted,&quot; or Type 1, fonts,electronic type foundries issued fonts in what was called the &quot;Type 3&quot;format.andP;  Type 1 fonts appeared better than Type 3 fonts at small sizes.andO;Evolution is one of a small but growing number of utilities that convert Type3 fonts into Type 1.andM;Greg Kolodziejzyk, Image Club's president, said Evolution lets users convertonly specified characters, rather than the entire type set.andP;  Also, charactersconverted by Evolution can be manipulated with PostScript drawing programssuch as Illustrator and Freehand.andM;(Daniel J. Rosenbaum/19901122)</TEXT></DOC>